VPC explanation overall how it works how request will go to a subnets, public & private subnets


How many clouds we have ? 1. service model 2. Deployment model(its has 4 models public, private, hybrid & community)


how VPC workflow works is
Internet Gate Way (IGW) it will send every request come from internet allows inside to it allows the request from internet to network, inside having a subnet that why 
request will go to first public subnet again here ROUTE TABLE will present here, Route table will allow request from the internet, next request will go to application,
(Network Address Translator)(NAT) what NAT will do is if the credentials all are correct means it will call to API, so through this NAT the request will go from public 
subnet to private subnet, in here private subnet having server application so finally this application output will show.

Subnets has 2 types 1. Public Subnet & 2. Private Subnet

IGW-------> ROUTE TABLE-----> PUBLIC SUBNET------>PRIVATE SUBNET

Lets create VPC like realtime below

search in AWS dashboard as VPC ------------> create vpc ---------> select vpc only --------> name: myvpc---------> IPv4 CIDR: 10.0.0.0/17 (CIDR block size must be 
